  "construction_rule": "30 probes for LC45 Jump Game II, 5 per manifold, 6 manifolds (naive_max_jump_suboptimal, single_large_jump_decoy, greedy_horizon_collapse, naive_max_jump_dead_landing, uniform_jump_array, greedy_frontier_valid_no_false_pressure). Probes are deterministic reachable `nums` lists (per the LC45 manifold descriptors) where the BFS oracle (lc45_brute_force) returns a finite jump count. Probe IDs p_lc45_0001..p_lc45_0030 assigned axis-by-axis in axis-declaration order. Split: O_obs = 15 probes at odd within-axis positions (1,3,5,...,29), D_target = 15 probes at even within-axis positions (2,4,6,...,30). This gives a 3+2+3+2+3+2 observed+held-out split per manifold (3,2,3,2,3,2 across the 6 manifolds in declaration order) for a balanced 15/15 total. All 30 probes empirically verified reachable (BFS raises on unreachable; no unreachable probes here). Truth values are computed by lc45_brute_force (LC45 ground truth) at freeze time. This is the Week 2 LC45 port of the protocol; the manifold descriptors are taken from the 6-manifold probe set for LC45 declared in the lc45 candidate corpus; specific probe values are reconstructed stubs chosen for reachability and manifold coverage, NOT derived from the protocol or any prior solver's outputs.",
